&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;**NEW WARD OPENING JANUARY 2021**&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse Opportunities – Inpatient Surgical Ward Ashford Hospital &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Theatres, Anesthetics, Surgery and Critical Care Division is undergoing an exciting time of expansion and transformation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Alongside the refurbishment and expansion of our existing theatre department on the Ashford Hospital site, Wordsworth Ward a 19 bedded area will open as the new acute surgical ward at Ashford. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ward will provide excellent evidence based care to patients primarily undergoing elective surgery for a wide range of procedures and will include short stay admissions and some longer stay admissions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We welcome applications from new graduates as well as experienced surgical nurses, or maybe you are looking for your first nursing role within the NHS and are looking to develop your nursing career or maybe you are an internal candidate looking to relocate to the Ashford site as your main base. Wherever you are in nursing journey we would love to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return we offer opportunities for training and development, access to the NHS Pension Scheme, work perks, NHS discounts, and opportunities for flexible working and access to onsite childcare provisions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We look forward to working with you on planning the next steps of your nursing career&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Matron Tracy Ockwell on 01932-723058. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
